EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO BUSINESSES AND PROFESSIONS -- PHARMACIES
***
1 This act would authorize pharmacists to dispense a one-time refill, for up to one hundred
2 days under the following conditions:
3 1. The pharmacist is unable to readily obtain a refill authorization from the prescriber, or
4 the patient does not have a prescriber;
5 2. The prescription is not for a drug in Schedule II-V
6 3. Medication is essential to maintain life or for a chronic condition;
7 4. The pharmacist has judged that stopping medication might produce undesirable health
8 risks or physical or mental discomfort; and
9 5. The pharmacist notifies the prescriber of the refill within seven business days, or if no
10 current prescriber exists, the pharmacist will maintain detailed records of the
11 transaction.
12 This act would take effect on July 1, 2025.
